## The Two Storacha Agents (PR #5)

```
┌──────────────────────────┐     ┌──────────────────────────┐
│   SERVER-SIDE AGENT      │     │   CLIENT-SIDE AGENT      │
│                          │     │                          │
│   Runs on: API routes    │     │   Runs on: Browser       │
│                          │     │                          │
│   Writes to:             │     │   Writes to:             │
│   • Platform space       │     │   • Group spaces         │
│     (avatars)            │     │     (via UCAN delegation)│
│   • Group spaces         │     │                          │
│     (manifests, bundles) │     │   Uploads:               │
│                          │     │   • Receipts             │
│   Has: Master keys       │     │   • Shared media         │
│                          │     │   • Group avatars        │
│                          │     │                          │
│                          │     │   Has: Delegated access  │
│                          │     │   per user per group     │
└──────────────────────────┘     └──────────────────────────┘
```

**Why two agents?**

- **Receipts and media** upload directly from the browser (client-side agent) for speed — no round-trip through the API server
- **Manifests and CAR bundles** are generated server-side (they require aggregating database records), so the server agent uploads them
- **User avatars** go through the server because they're processed (cropped/compressed) and stored in the platform space

