## How CIDs Flow Through the System

```
Receipt photo taken
    ↓
Client-side agent uploads to group space
    ↓
CID returned: bafy...bbb1
    ↓
Stored in DB: expense.receiptCid = "bafy...bbb1"
    ↓
Settlement happens, manifest generated
    ↓
Manifest JSON references bafy...bbb1
    ↓
Server agent uploads manifest to group space
    ↓
CID returned: bafy...ccc1
    ↓
Stored in DB: settlement.manifestCid = "bafy...ccc1"
    ↓
Cron job runs (every 24h)
    ↓
Fetches ALL CIDs: bafy...bbb1, bafy...ccc1, etc.
    ↓
Builds IPLD DAG referencing them (no re-upload, just references)
    ↓
Encodes as CAR file
    ↓
Server agent uploads CAR to group space
    ↓
Root CID returned: bafy...eee1
    ↓
Root CID anchored on-chain via SplitFareCIDRegistry
    ↓
Anyone can: root CID → fetch CAR → traverse DAG → verify every receipt
```

---

## Summary

| Space | Count | Owner | Contains |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Platform space** | 1 | Server agent | User avatars |
| **Group spaces** | 1 per group | Server agent (creator delegated) | Receipts, manifests, media, bundles, group avatar |

**Every piece of user content lives in a Storacha space.** The group space is the primary organizational unit — it's where the data ownership story lives, because a group's entire financial history is in one addressable, exportable, verifiable space.